               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām "Miracles of Mary" (fols. 4ra-118rb)
 I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 4ra-6va)
 I-2) ʾƎsaggǝd
                     laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsäkki... "I worship Thee..." (fols. 6va-7rb)
 I-3)
                     Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 7rb-9ra)
 I-4) Taʾammǝra Māryām
                     "Miracles of Mary": 151 miracles (fols. 9ra-118rb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 includes excerpts from Säʿatat za-lelit “Horologium for the
                        Night” (<locus from="5va" to="6rb">5va-6rb</locus>, with the hymn:</note>
                     <note>salām laki ḫoḫǝta mǝśrāq... “Salutation to you, Threshold of the East…”,
                           <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-3 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝlt ba-kǝlʾe Māryām... "O my Holy Lady Mary
                        and Two-fold Virgin..." (<locus target="#8rb">8rb-</locus>va)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos kahāli... "O my Lady,
                        Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ, the Almighty..." (<locus target="#8va">8va-</locus>) (cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān...
                        "Salutation to you, o my Lady Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the
                        Light..." (<locus from="8va" to="9ra">8va-9ra</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Text I-4 are numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
